I think now I understand your concern. In the plot you show, the residual term has \Lap c in the SplitCHParsed kernel. The description here is a bit confusing. In the actual code,  the \Lap c will be transformed into the \nabla c by taking the integral by part, so only gradient term will be remained. See the code below
Real
SplitCHCRes::computeQpResidual()
{
  Real residual =
      SplitCHBase::computeQpResidual(); //(f_prime_zero+e_prime)*_test[_i][_qp] from SplitCHBase

  residual += -_w[_qp] * _test[_i][_qp];
  residual += _kappa[_qp] * _grad_u[_qp] * _grad_test[_i][_qp];

  return residual;
}

After you understand this, you can follow @hugary1995 's comment to prove the split form will work for RZ coordinate system.
